Missing Value Imputation

Imputation Methods

  • Substitutaion with a measure of central tendency
    • : Missing value ( , outlier )
    1. Trimmed Mean ( ) : 5%
    2. Mid-minimum spacing
    • P percent of the data is trimmed from each tail of the distribution
    • From the trimmed distribution, \((Max + Min)/2\)
  • Distribution based
  • Tree Imputation
  • Regression Imputation
  • Imputation using the EM algorithm
  • Multiple Imputation
#install.packages("Hmisc", repos="http://cran.nexr.com")
library(Hmisc)
## Loading required package: lattice
## Loading required package: survival

R example

## Basic R functions ##
table(hmeq$REASON, hmeq$JOB)
##          
##            Mgr Office Other ProfExe Sales Self
##   DebtCon  572    620  1604     847    97   73
##   HomeImp  174    301   716     405    12  115
# dataframe    (   )
with(hmeq, table(REASON, JOB))  
##          JOB
## REASON     Mgr Office Other ProfExe Sales Self
##   DebtCon  572    620  1604     847    97   73
##   HomeImp  174    301   716     405    12  115
with(hmeq, table(REASON, JOB, useNA = "ifany"))
##          JOB
## REASON     Mgr Office Other ProfExe Sales Self <NA>
##   DebtCon  572    620  1604     847    97   73  115
##   HomeImp  174    301   716     405    12  115   57
##   <NA>      21     27    68      24     0    5  107
with(hmeq, table(REASON, JOB, exclude = "Other"))
##          JOB
## REASON    Mgr Office ProfExe Sales Self
##   DebtCon 572    620     847    97   73
##   HomeImp 174    301     405    12  115
#           (p-value = 0.004576 < 0.05)
chisq.test(table(hmeq$REASON, hmeq$BAD)) 
## 
##  Pearson's Chi-squared test with Yates' continuity correction
## 
## data:  table(hmeq$REASON, hmeq$BAD)
## X-squared = 8.0398, df = 1, p-value = 0.004576
#     
mosaicplot(~BAD+REASON, data=hmeq)

R plotting

#    bar chart  
plot(hmeq$JOB) 

#      pie chart 
pie(table(hmeq$JOB))

#  (BAD),   (DEBTINC)   Box plot   
#        (subset DEBTINC 75    )
plot(hmeq$BAD,hmeq$DEBTINC, subset=hmeq$DEBTINC<75)

#    plot 
plot(~BAD+DEBTINC, subset=DEBTINC<75, data=hmeq)

hist(hmeq$VALUE, breaks=50, freq=F, xlim=c(8000,300000))

hist(hmeq$VALUE, breaks=50, freq=F)#, xlim=c(8000,300000))
lines(density(hmeq$VALUE, na.rm=T), col='blue')

plot(~LOAN+VALUE+MORTDUE+YOJ+DEBTINC, data=hmeq, cex=0.1) # default size = 1 (cex    0.1 )

plot(~LOAN+VALUE+MORTDUE+YOJ+DEBTINC, data=hmeq, cex=0.1, subset = VALUE<300000, main="VALUE < 300000")

#log=1:3 ==> make 1:3 variables to log scale (LOAN, VALUE, MORTDUE   log   )
# () Value  Mortdue    ,           
plot(~LOAN+VALUE+MORTDUE+YOJ+DEBTINC, data=hmeq, cex=0.1, subset = VALUE<300000, log=1:3, main="Log scale")

require(MASS)
## Loading required package: MASS
color=rep('green',nrow(hmeq)) # rep=
color[hmeq$BAD==1]='red' # BAD=1(   RED )

# parcoord: parallel coordinate() 
# lwd=line width, lty=line type ( or .. etc)
parcoord(hmeq[,c('LOAN','VALUE','MORTDUE','CLAGE','DEBTINC')],col=color,lwd=0.001,lty=3)
